history.content:
I was enrolling this semester and it was a bit of a pain.

I phase 1'd 16a and was placed immediately on the waitlist, as seats were reserved for EECS freshman and all. As time progressed, my place on the waitlist didn't budge a bit, even around August. I was told that, because of budget cuts among other things, we may not be able to fit all students who enroll.

It wasn't until a week or so before classes where I got an email saying we can accept all declared CS majors due to expansion in classes.

I don't know if any of these circumstances will be present for Spring 2016 (an instructor could confirm this), but take these into consideration
